Yes, Book Keeper allows you to create and customize your own invoice templates using HTML and CSS. Go to Settings > Template Settings > Customize. Use <style> and </style> tags to write your custom CSS, which will override Book Keeper's default styles.

Examples:

1. **Increase Company Name Size**
<style>
.company-heading { font-size: 22px; text-align: center; }
</style>

2. **Change Table Heading Color**
<style>
#itemTable th {
  font-size: 16px;
  border: 1px solid #FF0000;
  border-radius: 1px 0 0;
  text-align: center;
  font-weight: bold;
  background-color: green;
  color: white;
}
</style>

3. **Custom Footer with Bank Details and Signatures**
Customization:
<style>
.cellborder { border: 1px solid #000; }
.footerTable { border-collapse: collapse; }
</style>

Footer:
<br><br>
<table border=1 cellspacing=2 width=100% class=footerTable>
<tr><td rowspan=4 class=cellborder>NOTE</td><td class=cellborder>1. All Payment should be made by NEFT/RTGS/ECS/Crossed Cheque drawn in favour of Creative Private Limited only.</td></tr>
<tr><td class=cellborder>2. Payment delay will incur interest @5% P.M.</td></tr>
<tr><td class=cellborder>3. Company not liable for unauthorized payees.</td></tr>
<tr><td class=cellborder>4. Disputes subject to Bangalore jurisdiction.</td></tr>
</table>

<table border=1 cellspacing=2 width=100% class=footerTable>
<tr><td rowspan=3 class=cellborder>BANK DETAIL<br>(For RTGS/NEFT/ECS)</td><td align=center colspan=4>Creative Private Limited</td></tr>
<tr><td class=cellborder>Account No</td><td class=cellborder>123456789</td><td class=cellborder>IFSC Code</td><td class=cellborder>PYTM0123456</td></tr>
<tr><td class=cellborder>Bank Name</td><td class=cellborder>SBI Bank</td><td class=cellborder>Branch</td><td class=cellborder>Bangalore</td></tr>
</table>

<br><br>
<table width=100%>
<tr><td width=30% align=center>Prepared By</td><td width=30% align=center>Checked By</td><td width=40% align=center>Authorized Signatory</td></tr>
</table>

4. **Add Border Lines After Each Item**
<style>
#itemTable td {
  border-left: 1px solid #000;
  border-right: 1px solid #000;
  border-top: 1px solid #000;
  border-bottom: 1px solid #000;
}
</style>

5. **Center the Company Logo (Template 1-3 only)**
<style>
.company-image { text-align: center; }
.company-image img { float: none; position: relative; }
</style>
